> Power yoga, power nap, power stance: all pretty important. But there's only one we'd choose to power up with at the end of the day, and that's this layered, textured, flavorful bowl. In it you'll find tender Turkish-spiced chicken over light and fluffy garlic-scallion quinoa, tossed with a tomato-cucumber salad topped with feta, more scallions, and a drizzle of creamy Greek yogurt sauce. Power(bowl) to the people!

== Aromatics and Quinoa ==

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic, scallion whites, and 1 tsp @Turkish Spice Blend{1%tbsp}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. (You'll use the rest of the Turkish Spice Blend later.)

Stir in 1 cup water (2 cups for 4), @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}; bring to a boil. Add @quinoa{1/2%cup} and stir to combine. Return to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low. Cover pot and simmer until quinoa is tender and water has absorbed, ~{16-18%minutes}.

== Salad ==

While quinoa cooks, trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch pieces. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, half the scallion greens, and half the @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}; you'll use the rest later. Season with salt and @pepper{to taste}.

== Greek Yogurt Sauce ==

In a second small bowl, combine @yogurt{2%tbsp}, remaining vinaigrette, and @sugar{1/4%tsp}; add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt, pepper, and remaining @Turkish Spice Blend{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken is on the thicker side, reduce heat to medium and cover; cook ~{5-7%minutes} on second side.

== Assembly ==

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{}; stir in half the salad. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide quinoa mixture between #bowls{2}; top with chicken and remaining salad. Sprinkle @feta cheese{1/2%cup} over bowls and drizzle with yogurt sauce. Garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.